<p>I have created a Chrome Web App.  I am able to send notifications to users who have installed the web app in Chrome through the Chrome Web Store.</p>  <p>I have read this documentation: <a href="https://developers.google.com/cloud-messaging/#send-msg" rel="nofollow">https://developers.google.com/cloud-messaging/#send-msg</a></p>  <p>That page references "Versatile Messaging Targets" and "Downstream Messaging".  I need to send a notification to the device (where web app was installed) and not to all devices where the users may be logged into.   </p>  <p>This page: <a href="https://developers.google.com/cloud-messaging/notifications" rel="nofollow">https://developers.google.com/cloud-messaging/notifications</a> says to send a request to: <a href="https://android.googleapis.com/gcm/notification" rel="nofollow">https://android.googleapis.com/gcm/notification</a></p>  <p>And this page:  <a href="https://developers.google.com/cloud-messaging/topic-messaging" rel="nofollow">https://developers.google.com/cloud-messaging/topic-messaging</a> says to send a request to <a href="https://gcm-http.googleapis.com/gcm/send" rel="nofollow">https://gcm-http.googleapis.com/gcm/send</a></p>  <p>To send a message to a device should I use  <a href="https://android.googleapis.com/gcm/notification" rel="nofollow">https://android.googleapis.com/gcm/notification</a> only?</p>